  "body": "### Description\n\nGraphQL multipart request specification is a interoperable [multipart form](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7578) field structure for GraphQL requests, used by various file upload client/server implementations.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/jaydenseric/graphql-multipart-request-spec\r\n\r\nItâ€™s possible to implement:\r\n\r\n- Nesting files anywhere within operations (usually in variables).\r\n- Operation batching.\r\n- File deduplication.\r\n- File upload streams in resolvers.\r\n- Aborting file uploads in resolvers\r\n\r\nAlthough not a real standard or official specification, it's supported by a lot of client libraries (`urql`, `apollo`, `apollo-android` ....) and it would be great to have such support also in quarkus\r\n\r\n\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\nSee PR",
